"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-07-27-fans-mistakenly-claim-performers-testicle-seen-olympics-opening-ceremony-21310234\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Viewers of theOlympicsopening ceremony thought they'd spotted a major wardrobe malfunction as a performer's testicle appeared to be on show.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 140, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In one of the more bizarre segments of the opening ceremony inParison Friday night, Philippe Katerine, a French singer-songwriter, was covered head to toe in blue body paint as he was unveiled by a giant cloche.\", \"from\": 142, \"to\": 353, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 226, \"end\": 243, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippe_Katerine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Philippe Katerine\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippe_Katerine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippe_Katerine\"}, {\"begin\": 247, \"end\": 253, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9920577648780751, \"rank\": 0.004107563311018228, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Katerine, who also had a bright orange beard, was wearing a fruit headdress and sash, and was meant to be portraying theGreekgod Dionysus, although that may have been lost on many of the viewers.\", \"from\": 355, \"to\": 550, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 484, \"end\": 492, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.788047609532715e-14, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But as Katerine began singing, viewers could not help but notice that one of the background performers wearing a black jacket appeared to have a testicle popping out of his pants as he stood motionless.\", \"from\": 552, \"to\": 754, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The performer and his rogue piece of flesh was on show for nearly 30 seconds before Katerine's bed of fruit and flowers covered their genital area.\", \"from\": 756, \"to\": 903, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, while many were convinced that a testicle was on show for the millions watching around the world and pictures of the incident have gone viral on social media, the reality is that it was a simple wardrobe malfunction involving the performer's tights.\", \"from\": 905, \"to\": 1163, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A round hole in the black tights started out as testicle-shaped when Katerine began his song but as the performer unfroze and danced, it became clear that the split was becoming bigger.\", \"from\": 1165, \"to\": 1350, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Later into the performance which then focused on a dance troupe who were floating along the River Seine, the camera cut back to Katerine's background performers dancing to the music.\", \"from\": 1352, \"to\": 1534, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1444, \"end\": 1455, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By that time, the hole in the performer's black tights had ripped across nearly the entire front part of their right thigh.\", \"from\": 1536, \"to\": 1659, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was not the only gaffe during a rain-soaked opening ceremonyas the Olympic flag was raised upside down.\", \"from\": 1661, \"to\": 1767, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Earlier in the ceremony, the South Korea team were incorrectly introduced as athletes were put on boats and driven down the Seine.\", \"from\": 1769, \"to\": 1899, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1804, \"end\": 1809, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"score\": 0.9932927741634581, \"rank\": 0.003169424390386783, \"text\": \"Korea\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\"}, {\"begin\": 1893, \"end\": 1898, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9995114433915007, \"rank\": 0.000488675873621747, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Unfortunately, South Korea were announced as 'the Democratic People's Republic of Korea' - which is the full name of North Korea.\", \"from\": 1901, \"to\": 2030, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1916, \"end\": 1927, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"score\": 0.9999999365200003, \"rank\": 5.2119052380202764e-08, \"text\": \"South Korea\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\"}, {\"begin\": 2018, \"end\": 2029, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Korea\", \"score\": 0.9999999844199011, \"rank\": 1.5332449344845095e-08, \"text\": \"North Korea\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Korea\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The South Korean sports ministry has said it planned to submit a 'strong complaint with France on a government level' over the error.\", \"from\": 2032, \"to\": 2165, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2042, \"end\": 2048, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language\", \"score\": 0.9999141333775005, \"rank\": 8.4711215491654e-05, \"text\": \"Korean\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2120, \"end\": 2126, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9918552212577093, \"rank\": 0.004193525577699271, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'We deeply apologise for the mistake that occurred when introducing the Korean team during the opening ceremony broadcast,' the International Olympic Committee (IOC) said in a post in Korean on X.  IOC president, Thomas Bach, also plans to meet with South Korea's leader, Yoon Suk-yeol, over the mistake.\", \"from\": 2167, \"to\": 2471, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2239, \"end\": 2245, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language\", \"score\": 0.9999141333775005, \"rank\": 8.4711215491654e-05, \"text\": \"Korean\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2295, \"end\": 2332, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 2295, \"end\": 2332, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 2351, \"end\": 2357, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language\", \"score\": 0.9999141333775005, \"rank\": 8.4711215491654e-05, \"text\": \"Korea